SECTION 7: SUPPORT & SUCCESS POSITIONING IDEAS

These ideas position premium support and success services as subscription benefit.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

IDEA #29: "Premium Support - Professional Subscribers Get Dedicated Help"

Positioning Message: "Professional plan = Priority support, faster response times"
Subscription Model Angle: Support tier tied to subscription level
Target Audience: Companies wanting peace of mind, support-focused buyers
Psychology: Premium support = peace of mind, problem resolution
Key Message: "Professional subscribers: 2-hour response time. Basic: 24 hours."
Why It Works: Support quality matters to serious buyers

Implementation:
• Basic: Email support, 24-hour response
• Professional: Chat support, 2-hour response
• Enterprise: Dedicated account manager, 30-min response, phone support
• Support quality: "Professional subscribers get faster answers"
• Upgrade messaging: "Need faster support? Professional plan includes it."

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

IDEA #30: "Success Team Included - Professional Gets Personal Hiring Strategist"

Positioning Message: "Professional plan includes onboarding and strategic guidance"
Subscription Model Angle: Success services bundled with Premium subscription
Target Audience: Companies wanting success guarantee, strategic guidance
Psychology: "We're invested in your success" message
Key Message: "Professional includes quarterly hiring strategy review with our expert"
Why It Works: Removes fear of "I won't know how to use this"

Implementation:
• Basic: Self-serve, online help docs
• Professional: Onboarding call, monthly strategy email
• Enterprise: Dedicated success manager, quarterly strategy reviews, 1-on-1 guidance
• Messaging: "Professional includes access to our hiring experts"
• Value: "Quarterly guidance = $5,000 consulting value, included free"

