SECTION 10: CONTENT STRATEGY FOR SUBSCRIPTION POSITIONING

For each positioning idea, create:

Content Format 1: LANDING PAGE (1 per idea)
├─ Length: 1000-1500 words
├─ Focus: Explain positioning, show value, drive CTA
├─ CTA: "Start free trial" or "Request demo"
└─ Example: "Pay Per Hire Model Landing Page"

Content Format 2: COMPARISON CONTENT (1 per tier)
├─ Format: "Basic vs Professional vs Enterprise" comparison
├─ Format: "Why Top Companies Upgrade to Professional"
└─ Format: "Cost Comparison: Manual Hiring vs Ecoskiller Professional"

Content Format 3: BENEFIT-FOCUSED CONTENT (2-3 per idea)
├─ Format: LinkedIn posts, blog articles
├─ Focus: Specific benefit explanation
└─ Example: "Why Professional Subscribers Hire 40% Faster"

Content Format 4: CUSTOMER SUCCESS STORIES (3-5 stories)
├─ Format: Case studies showing journey and results
├─ Focus: Basic → Professional → Enterprise progression
└─ Example: "How Startup Scaled From Free to Enterprise in 12 Months"

Content Format 5: INTERACTIVE CONTENT (3-5 tools)
├─ Format: ROI calculator, feature comparison, plan selector
├─ Focus: Self-serve decision making
└─ Example: "Plan Selector: Find Your Perfect Tier"

Content Format 6: TESTIMONIALS & PROOF (10-15 videos)
├─ Format: 60-90 second customer testimonials
├─ Focus: Real results, plan progression stories
└─ Example: "Professional Subscriber Testimonial Series"

Total Initial Content: 30-40 pieces across all 30 ideas

